HEADWORD: Heptavalent
<hw>Hep*tav"a*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hepta-</ets> + L. <ets>valens</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Valence</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having seven units of
attractive force or affinity; -- said of <xex>heptad</xex> elements or
radicals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

